Housing fire in helmet Brecht: Rescue squad saves charred corpse
The fire-brigade had to disengage on late Thursday evening in helmet Brecht.
A three-family house in the district yard catches fires at the night to Friday.
The rescue squad saves a charred corpse from the house.
Rescue squad found with a fire into of helmet Brecht a charred corpse in a three-family house.
Whether it concerns an inhabitant is still unclearly, as a spokesman of the police in Bayreuth said.
On late Thursday evening it had burned in the ground floor of the house.
When the fire-brigade arrived, the flames already struck from a window.
The task forces went into the apartment and found the corpse in a room.
This and a further room burned out completely.
The entire ground floor was damaged.
All other inhabitants were during the fire not at home, continued to explain the police spokesman.
The building is for the time being no longer habitable.
The exact cause for the fire was not first clear.
